&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Executive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Austin, TX (Hybrid, 3 days/week onsite)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Togetherwork is a $250M recurring revenue SaaS business with over 33 software applications serving 12+ vertical markets. We exist to help communities, organizations, and businesses thrive by delivering software solutions tailored to their unique needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With our new headquarters on South Congress in Austin, TX, we are entering an exciting phase of growth. We work hard and play hard. We love our customers, we innovate with purpose, and we won’t stop until we’ve delighted every client across the diverse ecosystem we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Togetherwork is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;Account Executive &lt;/strong&gt;on our Smartwaiver product line &lt;strong&gt;to expand our customer base by &lt;/strong&gt;identifying, engaging, and closing high-value prospects. This role mainly fields inbound leads to achieve quota attainment. This role focuses on acquiring multi-location businesses, large national organizations, and Private Equity-backed companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll play a key role in driving new logo growth through a proactive, consultative sales approach—leveraging outreach, video meetings, and in-person engagements. This is a high-impact opportunity for a results-oriented sales professional who thrives in building relationships and closing complex deals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field inbound leads through website, webinars, trade shows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively manage leads throughout the entire sales cycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead outreach and nurturing to assigned market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify and Identify prospect needs by leveraging key contacts within an organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct phone and web-based sales presentations and product demos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn the tools necessary to be successful: CRM, scripts, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn Sales Navigator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Salesforce to manage prospect pipeline and provide accurate sales forecasts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel to represent Smartwaiver and industry tradeshows (2-3 times per year)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of inbound and outbound sales experience, B2B preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in a mixed inbound (80%) and outbound sales motion (20%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating in a high-velocity sales environment where speed-to-lead and responsiveness impact results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to learn and adopt new platforms and tools (e.g., Salesforce, HubSpot, ZoomInfo, LinkedIn Sales Navigator).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to explain complex solutions to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and time management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of achieving or exceeding sales goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who takes initiative and performs well with limited direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Success-driven, collaborative team player who thrives in a dynamic, fast-changing environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coachable, resilient, and comfortable receiving direct feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to industry trade shows as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why This Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact:&lt;/strong&gt; Play a critical role in Togetherwork’s growt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.375rem] font-bold&quot;&gt;Account Manager (Accountant) (Remote - EST/CST)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;Account Manager (Accountant)&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Remote (U.S. — Eastern and Central Time Zones Only)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation: up to $95,000 USD per year&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;We are looking for a full-time Accountant - Client Services Manager to join our growing team. This position supports a portfolio of clients by overseeing all areas relating to their general ledger. Working directly with client staff and lay leaders, the Accountant - Client Services Manager is expected to take initiative in maintaining each client&#39;s financial health and serve as a trusted accounting resource across their organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Provide accurate and timely monthly financial reporting including balance sheets and profit and loss statements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Assist clients with budget entry, expense tracking, and monthly contributions management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Work closely with internal AP and AR team members to oversee accurate bank reconciliations and ensure precision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Manage year-end 1099 preparation for vendors and collaborate with the Accounts Payable Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Maintain client-specific documentation, standardize bookkeeping for new clients, and track and complete custom projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Communicate regularly with clients through email and meetings, support clients during audits or financial reviews, and actively participate in team meetings and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;text-text-100 mt-2 -mb-1 text-base font-bold&quot;&gt;What You&#39;ll Bring&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Accounting with 5+ years of accounting experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Extensive experience in bookkeeping, financial reporting, budgeting, General Ledger systems, and external audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Proficiency in Excel, O365, and QuickBooks with demonstrated success managing multiple clients and projects simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Outstanding customer service skills and effective communication, both written and oral, with a strong ability to synthesize financial information for non-finance audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Adaptability, self-motivation, exceptional attention to detail, and the ability

&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Marketing Manager - Austin, TX&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;We are looking for a Brand Marketing Manager to serve as the operational backbone of our Brand &amp;amp; Communications team within our Marketing organization. This role is responsible for owning creative operations, brand consistency, and the systems and workflows that enable a lean team to deliver high-quality output across a portfolio of 25+ vertical software brands. The Brand Manager partners closely with Marketing, Product, and Growth teams to ensure every brand touchpoint feels cohesive—scaling creative output through smart processes and AI-assisted tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Creative Operations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Own end-to-end creative workflow management, including intake, routing, prioritization, and delivery across all brands in the portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Keep projects moving and stakeholders informed across multiple concurrent workstreams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Manage relationships with external creative partners, freelancers, and agencies—briefing, reviewing, and integrating their work into the broader portfolio workflow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Build and maintain systems that others can run, not just complete tasks yourself&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Brand Strategy Execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Translate brand strategy into day-to-day creative execution across campaigns, product launches, and partner materials for sub-brands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Build, maintain, and continuously improve the Canva and AI-assisted design template library so teams can self-serve on-brand assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Identify opportunities to standardize and scale creative output across the portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]&quot;&gt;Brand Governance &amp;amp; Quality&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;[li_&amp;amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Serve as the first line of quality review on brand outputs—enforce guidelines, flag deviations, and maintain a living brand standards resource for the broader team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal

&lt;h1&gt;Client Solutions Manager&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Remote (U.S.-based)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Type: Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Togetherwork, we empower mission-driven organizations with cutting-edge software solutions. Our clients include some of the world’s most impactful nonprofits—like the ASPCA (American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals), ACLU (American Civil Liberties Union), and International Rescue Committee. We’re passionate about helping them succeed through innovative technology and exceptional service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Client Solutions Manager to lead the implementation and ongoing success of our fundraising and advocacy software. You’ll serve as a strategic partner to nonprofit clients, guiding them through complex technical projects, from onboarding and integrations to feature adoption and support.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is a client-facing, cross-functional role ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technology, project management, and customer success. The role is a blend of two responsibilities: structured project management (planning, scoping, and driving implementations and projects to completion) and hands-on client support (responding to requests, troubleshooting, and training). You should be energized by both, and comfortable shifting between leading a project and resolving a day-to-day support ticket. Because this work is billable, it also calls for precise, detail-oriented tracking and reporting of your time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for nonprofit clients throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead software implementations, system integrations, and technical consulting engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with external partners (design agencies, customer relationship management (CRM) consultants, email service provider (ESP) vendors) to deliver holistic solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business needs into technical requirements, timelines, and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide clients through complex decisions that align with their strategic goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate cross-functional teams of developers and producers to ensure timely, high-quality project delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor project scope, budget, and deliverables to ensure alignment with Statements of Work (SOW).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide proactive, high-touch day-to-day support and training to drive client satisfaction and product adoption. This support work carries equal weight to project delivery and is a core, ongoing part of the role, not an occasional add-on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately track and log billable time in 15-minute increments across both projects and support work, ensuring timely, detailed, and reliable time entries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage&amp;nbsp;approved AI tools, automation, and data dashboards to support solution analysis, planning, documentation, and risk identification, and to inform delivery recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share feedback and adopt evolving AI-enabled delivery practices and solution standards to help improve how the team works.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Bring&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in or with nonprofit organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with fundraising, digital marketing, and advocacy strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong project management skills with the ability to juggle multiple client engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical fluency with content management systems (CMS), enterprise CRM (eCRM), ESPs, and fundraising tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Salesforce (especially Nonprofit Success Pack (NPSP) or Nonprofit Cloud).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with project management tools like Jira and Monday.com.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pro

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
